The paper presents an algorithm for solving linear programs with a focus on the maximum flow problem, which involves graph algorithms and numerical linear algebra. Therefore, it is likely to be classified under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The paper also involves numerical methods for solving linear systems, which falls under cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Finally, the paper presents a new self-concordant barrier function, which is a topic in convex optimization and falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning).
